      "callEndedTimestamp": null,
      "isPinned": false,
      "content": "# Lets get you out of div 5\n\nFirst thing to note is i will be basing qual of eu qual which is top 400\n\n# Estimated qual\nThe estimated qual is around 250 - 270 points (270 points to be safe)\n\nKey Priorities\n- You should be aiming to hit everyendgame in order to maximise placement points. Do not braindead key as this can lead to bad outcomes in the game aswell. \n- Midgame, should be focused on good set up for the endgame where if you want you take smart fights not ones 500 meters in zone. In addition please focus on maintaining your materials or increasing them \n- Choosing a good drop spot for your playstyle, what I mean by this is: if you're a placement warrior, go land at low-key drops that have a few chests and are likely uncontested. However, if you feel you're good at taking fights and like fighting off-spawn, land at a named POI to get good loot and give yourself a better chance in midgame and endgame. However, both playstyles have their weaknesses and strengths, so one is not superior to the other.\n- In your endgame you should be focusing trying to get height. Height in these lobbies is crucial as it is likely the most easist layer for most teams to play as there is miminal pressure from other teams compared to mindground and low ground. In addition you are able to pick of easy kills on height as well.\n- You should be aiming to win every game. It sounds simple, but what I mean is that you shouldn’t be W-keying randomly. Prioritize placement more as your not needing at top 10 placement here but top 400 where consistency will reward",
